      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver must demonstrate correct numerical implementation through comparison with manufactured or analytical solutions for relevant flow regimes.",
      "rationale": "Method of manufactured solutions applied to the power-law hemolysis transport equation embedded in the solver UDF. Numerical error in scalar transport confirmed below 0.5% for representative Reynolds and Schmidt numbers. Code verification report CV-2024-03 on file."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index must be below 5% for the primary quantity of interest (RH) at the nominal operating point.",
      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study performed at 4 L/min / 3000 RPM. GCI = 1.4% for RH. Medium mesh (5.8M cells) selected for production runs as the best balance of accuracy and computational cost. See ValidationResult hemolysis-mesh-sensitivity-02."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Conditions under which validation data were collected must be documented and compared to COU operating envelope; material deviations must be assessed.",
      "rationale": "The multi-site observational study recorded pump speeds, flow rates, fluid temperature, and haematocrit for each circuit. Operating conditions span the COU envelope of 2–6 L/min and 2000–4000 RPM. Mean haematocrit 33% (±4%) is consistent with CPB clinical practice. Temperature variation ±3 °C introduces less than 2% variability in viscosity; sensitivity analysis confirms negligible effect on RH."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Predicted QoI values must agree with measured values within 15% MAPE; systematic bias must be characterised.",
      "rationale": "MAPE across five operating points is 8.3%. Bland-Altman analysis shows mean bias of +0.02 RH units (slight over-prediction) with limits of agreement ±0.09 RH units. No operating-point-specific outliers exceed the 15% threshold. Bias direction is conservative (over-predicts hemolysis), which is acceptable for safety assessment."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The QoI used in validation (RH) must be the same metric used in the regulatory submission acceptance criterion.",
      "rationale": "The relative hemolysis index RH is the primary regulatory metric per FDA guidance on CPB device submissions. Validation data directly measure RH via the same spectrophotometric protocol used in predicate device testing. No surrogate QoI substitution was made."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activities must cover the geometry, operating conditions, and fluid properties relevant to the COU.",
      "rationale": "Validation data were collected on the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry — the same geometry used in the CFD model. Operating conditions span the full COU envelope. Bovine blood and validated blood analogue data are both available, with the bovine blood subset providing the primary comparison. Geometric fidelity confirmed by coordinate measurement machine (CMM) report CMM-2024-11."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not assessed at MRL 2 for this factor; iterative convergence monitoring sufficient.",
      "rationale": "At MRL 2, formal numerical solver error quantification beyond residual monitoring is not required. Residuals converged to 1e-5 for all equations; mass imbalance below 0.01%. Scoped out per MRL 2 assessment matrix."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not assessed at MRL 2; analyst training records reviewed as sufficient control.",
      "rationale": "Analyst team completed ANSYS Fluent advanced training (certification on file). Simulation setup checklist followed per SOP-CFD-04. Formal use-error quantification not required at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The turbulence and hemolysis model forms must be justified for the flow regimes present in the CPB pump.",
      "rationale": "Reynolds-averaged Navier-Stokes with SST k-omega turbulence closure selected based on published benchmark studies for centrifugal blood pumps (Hariharan et al. 2011; Fraser et al. 2012). Power-law hemolysis model (Giersiepen et al.) implemented as a scalar transport UDF. Model form uncertainty estimated at ±12% RH based on literature comparison; within acceptable range for MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Key model inputs (viscosity, density, hemolysis model constants) must be traceable to characterised sources with documented uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "Blood viscosity modelled as non-Newtonian (Carreau-Yasuda) with parameters from Gijsen et al. (1999); density 1055 kg/m³. Hemolysis model constants from Arora et al. (2004) calibration dataset. Input uncertainty propagation via ±10% perturbation of each constant shows RH sensitivity below 5% for all inputs. Input traceability documented in model input register MIR-2024-06."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not assessed at MRL 2; sample characterisation documentation reviewed.",
      "rationale": "Bovine blood lots used in the observational study were characterised for haematocrit and mean corpuscular fragility index. Formal statistical sample adequacy assessment not required at MRL 2. Lot characterisation reports on file."
    },
